opentermix (0.2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add an Upload button to the SFTP browser, alongside a redrawn Download
    icon.
  * Add SSH port tunneling (Local/Remote/Dynamic-SOCKS) from the Sessions
    panel, with an active-tunnels tab next to terminal/Settings tabs.
  * Fix the terminal font defaulting to Bold Italic on first launch; font
    changes are now saved immediately instead of only on a clean exit.
  * Fix ssh/sftp connections targeting the resolved HostName instead of the
    ~/.ssh/config alias: any Host-block option not explicitly modeled by
    OpenTermix (ProxyCommand, a non-default IdentityFile, ...) was silently
    ignored, breaking connections that rely on it (e.g. routing through Tor,
    or a per-host key) even though a manual `ssh <alias>` worked fine.
    Affects terminals, tunnels, and the SFTP browser.
  * Packaging: add pkg-config to Build-Depends and qt6-svg-plugins to
    Depends (the SVG icon engine used by the toolbar icons isn't picked up
    by dpkg-shlibdeps); drop the stale debian/install file left over from
    before dh_auto_install started installing straight into
    debian/opentermix.
  * Packaging: support building for Ubuntu (26.04+) in addition to Debian
    (trixie+) - debian/control now accepts either qtermwidget dev package
    name (libqtermwidget-dev | libqtermwidget6-2-dev), and
    scripts/build-deb.sh generalizes the debootstrap-chroot build to any
    Debian or Ubuntu target. Older Ubuntu releases (22.04, 24.04) aren't
    supported: Ubuntu doesn't yet ship a Qt6 build of qtermwidget for them
    and won't backport one into an already-released LTS.

 -- maile <maile@debian>  Mon, 20 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0300

